        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 4:56PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of I-10 Near The Kimble-Kerr County Line, or 12 miles
east of Segovia. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Kimble
and southwestern Mason Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
